snippet.textDisplay:
We must not underestimate the danger of the Coronavirus. Many people threw caution to the wind during historical pandemics. We must not repeat the same mistakes.

We all know by now that we must not leave our homes unless it is absolutely essential. Even then, we must be very careful.

One thing we can all do that might help would be to eat a little less food than we normally would. This will help our food supplies last longer and help reduce our need to travel to the shops as often.
For example - if you normally eat 2x eggs for breakfast, you can change to eating just 1x egg. If you would normally have 2x slices of toast, you could change to eating just 1x slice of toast. Small simple changes can help make a difference.
